In a bid to rid Aba and environs of waste, the Abia State governor, Okezie Ikpeazu, has said it will begin street by street collection of wastes from 5pm on a daily basis. <img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-1236674" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/waste.jpg?resize=300%2C191&#038;ssl=1" alt="Abia, waste" width="300" height="191" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/waste.jpg?resize=300%2C191&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/waste.jpg?resize=768%2C489&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/waste.jpg?resize=1024%2C653&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/waste.jpg?resize=58%2C37&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/waste.jpg?resize=260%2C166&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/waste.jpg?resize=200%2C127&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/waste.jpg?resize=560%2C357&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/waste.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/waste.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> He stated that the indiscriminate disposal of wastes would no longer be allowed, adding that anyone caught disposing wastes outside the approved designated points will be arrested. Ikpeazu had declared a state of emergency on sanitation in response to the increasing challenges of waste management in the State. The Governor promised to take over and coordinate the management activities in Aba Metropolis to restore sanity and discipline for a month period. Ikpeazu further pledged to create distinct waste management authorities in Aba North, Aba South, Osisioma Ngwa, Obingwa, Ugwunagbo, Umuahia South and Umuahia North council areas. “Local Government waste managers shall be appointed immediately to oversee these management authorities in the specified Local Government Areas,” a statement from his Chief Press Secretary, Onyebuchi Ememanka, said. Meanwhile, evacuation of refuse had begun in Aba and Umuahia areas. Vanguard As Abia State governor, Dr. Okezie Ikpeazu enters the second week in office, there are growing concerns over enormous challenges to be tackled. June 9, 2015 In "News" FOR many years Aba, the commercial nerve centre of Abia State, was a byword for a dirty city on account of the mountains of waste from both industrial and domestic concerns that became signposts in different parts of the city. Indeed, any visitor to Aba then was sure to be… September 26, 2013 In "Metro" DR. Okezie Ikpeazu mounted the saddle of leadership in Abia State on May 29, 2015, on a promising note amid huge expectations. January 1, 2018 In "News"